# Khonkholoy, Mukhorshibirsky District, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Khonkholoy () is a rural locality (a selo) in Mukhorshibirsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 1,590 as of 2010. There are 18 streets.
Geography
Khonkholoy is located 29&nbsp;km northeast of Mukhorshibir (the district's administrative centre) by road. Nikolsk is the nearest rural locality.
